{
  "texts": [
    "Some recent work has also explored using large language models in few-shot settings for counterfactual generation [13].",
    "Unlike previous work, in this paper, we focus on zero-shot counterfactual generation for stress-testing text classifiers.",
    "b) Large Language Models and Applications in NLP: Large Language Models (LLMs) are usually transformer-based models capable of generating human-like text.",
    "Recent examples of large language models include the GPT family of models from OpenAI [14]- [16], the Llama family of models from Meta [17]- [19], Gemini from Google [20], etc.",
    "A general training recipe for training LLMs include an unsupervised pretraining step, where the model is trained using a huge corpora of text, typically comprising of text from the internet [21], [22], followed by one or more supervised fine-tuning steps, such as instruction-tuning [23], [24]."
  ]
}